+# Documentation & Onboarding — Review
+
+**Status:** Reviewed
+**Lane:** `documentation-and-onboarding`
+**Date:** 2026-03-22
+**Reviewer:** Nemesis review process
+
+## Verdict
+
+**Conditional pass.** The documentation is structurally complete, mostly accurate,
+and covers the right surface area for a first slice. Three issues must be fixed
+before this lane can close: the false "encrypted" claim, the missing CORS headers
+that break the documented quickstart, and the `observe`/`control` typo in the
+README. The remaining findings are improvement recommendations and security
+advisories for operator awareness.
+
+---
+
+## Correctness Findings
+
+### C1 — BLOCKER: "Encrypted" claim is false
+
+`docs/architecture.md:140` describes the event spine as "Append-only encrypted
+event journal." `spine.py` line 3 has the same docstring. The implementation
+writes plaintext JSON to a JSONL file with no encryption whatsoever.
+
+The product spec (Layer 3) describes encryption as an aspirational architectural
+boundary. The documentation describes the current milestone 1 implementation as
+if encryption already exists. This is dishonest to operators and contributors.
+
+**Fix:** Remove the word "encrypted" from `docs/architecture.md` and `spine.py`.
+Replace with "append-only event journal" and add a note: "Encryption at rest is
+defined in the product spec but not yet implemented in milestone 1."
+
+### C2 — BLOCKER: No CORS headers breaks the documented quickstart
+
+`daemon.py` `_send_json()` (line 162) sets only `Content-Type: application/json`.
+No `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` header is sent. The documented quickstart tells
+users to open `index.html` via `file://` or from `python3 -m http.server 9000`,
+then the HTML makes `fetch()` calls to `http://127.0.0.1:8080`.
+
+In modern browsers, `file://` → `http://localhost` and
+`http://host:9000` → `http://host:8080` are cross-origin requests. Without CORS
+headers, these requests will be blocked. The spec claims "All curl examples
+confirmed working" but curl does not enforce CORS — only browsers do.
+
+**Fix:** Add `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` to `_send_json()` in daemon.py
+(acceptable for LAN-only milestone 1), or add a `do_OPTIONS` handler for
+preflight. Then re-verify the quickstart in Chrome and Firefox.
+
+### C3 — BLOCKER: README capability description is wrong
+
+`README.md:88` says:
+> `observe` / `control` capabilities | Minimal scope. Control-only clients can
+> monitor. Control-only can command.
+
+This should read: "Observe-only clients can monitor. Control-capable clients can
+command." The current text says "Control-only" twice.
+
+**Fix:** Correct the table cell.
+
+### C4 — Minor: `ZEND_TOKEN_TTL_HOURS` documented but doesn't exist in code
+
+`docs/operator-quickstart.md:61` documents a `ZEND_TOKEN_TTL_HOURS` environment
+variable with default `24`. This variable is not read anywhere in the Python
+codebase. The operator quickstart should either remove this row or clearly label
+it as "reserved, not yet implemented."
+
+### C5 — Minor: `ThreadedHTTPS` typo in architecture diagram
+
+`docs/architecture.md:323` says `ThreadedHTTPS` in the system diagram. The class
+is `ThreadedHTTPServer` and there is no TLS. Should read `ThreadedHTTP`.
+
+### C6 — Minor: `cli.py status` inconsistent `--client` documentation
+
+`docs/operator-quickstart.md:115-116` shows `cli.py status` without `--client`.
+`docs/api-reference.md:278` shows it with `--client`. Both are valid — the flag
+is optional — but this should be stated explicitly in the API reference to avoid
+confusion.
+
+### C7 — Minor: `file://` pairing suggestion is misleading
+
+`docs/operator-quickstart.md:139` suggests opening
+`file:///opt/zend/apps/zend-home-gateway/index.html` to pair a phone. A phone
+cannot access a `file://` path on a remote server. This only works if the HTML is
+copied to the phone itself. The HTTP server method (line 146) is the correct
+approach for LAN pairing. The file URL suggestion should be removed or clearly
+scoped to "on the server's own browser."
+
+### C8 — Minor: `genesis/plans/001-master-plan.md` does not exist
+
+This file was listed as a review input but the `genesis/` directory does not
+exist in the repository. The closest equivalent is
+`plans/2026-03-19-build-zend-home-command-center.md`. No action required on the
+docs themselves, but the lane input manifest was wrong.
